#
# framespam
# Frame Spammer (c) 2007, Matej Sustr
#

Allows to send an arbitrary raw frame using an IEEE 802.11 wireless card
adapter in monitor mode.


# Compilation and installation

	make
	make install	(requires root privileges)


#
# Usage
#########

You must be root to send raw frames.

	framespam -i <ifname> [-n <num] [-d <delay>] < file

-i <ifname>	Interface to send frames through, this must be a wireless
		ethernet adapter in monitor mode, using an injection-enabled
		driver.

-n <num>	Send the frame <num> times, defaults to infinite.

-d <delay>	Delay between sending frames in microseconds. Defaults to
		10000.

file		Program reads the frame to be sent using standard input,
		which may be redirected from a file.

Program may be terminated by pressing Ctrl-C.


